[PATCH] Enable pseudowires for LDP L2VPN

From: TertoOS <eduardoterto@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 21:30:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] SONiC-ONLY Enable pseudowires for LDP L2VPN

FRR ldpd ships with stubs for the l2vpn ATOM table but rejects
activating a pseudowire ("Incomplete config, specify lsr-id" — yet
that command path is gone) unless `--enable-pseudowires` is given
at configure time. TertoOS uses canonical-mpls validation to drive
PE-to-PE pseudowires (PPPoE backhaul over MPLS), so the flag has
to be on.

Adds `--enable-pseudowires` alongside the existing ldpd-related
options. No other configure change.

---
 debian/rules |    1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/debian/rules b/debian/rules
--- a/debian/rules
+++ b/debian/rules
@@ -76,6 +76,7 @@ override_dh_auto_configure:
 		--enable-multipath=514 \
 		--enable-pcre2posix \
 		\
+		--enable-pseudowires \
 		--enable-user=frr \
